  <prompt>
    Extend `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]` shape to carry the enriched fields per architecture ┬¦11.2 ŌĆö `SummaryText`, `ClassifiedDocType`, `ClassifiedConfidence`, `Sections`, `TableMetadata`, `Citations`, `PageCount`, `Language`. Follow the R6 task 051 `SaveTabsAsync` precedent: add fields to existing record/class additively, ensure JSON serialization is backward-compat (existing sessions without these fields deserialize cleanly with defaults).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in `ChatSession` persistence shape + JSON backward-compat patterns.</role>

  <goal>
    `ChatSession.cs` (or `ChatSessionFile.cs`) extended with the 8 enriched fields. Cosmos JSON serialization round-trips cleanly: existing session docs (no enriched fields) deserialize with field defaults; new sessions roundtrip enriched fields. Unit test confirms backward-compat.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture ┬¦11.2 (What to extend): `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[N]` adds enriched fields. The pattern precedent is R6 task 051's `SaveTabsAsync` (extended `StoredSession` with `Tabs` + `WidgetStates` fields the same way). The shape is consumed by:
      - `SessionPersistenceService.UpdateUploadedFilesAsync` (task 072)
      - `LayeredContextCardBuilder` (task 076)
      - `list_session_files` tool (task 083)
      - `get_file_manifest` tool (task 084)
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
